{% endfor %}
</user_clarifying_answers>

<task>
Generate a complete MVP PRD for this Platform/Marketplace. Follow the A3 template structure.
</task>

<a3_specific_sections>
1. Platform Sides: Define each side (buyers, sellers, etc.), priority side for MVP, initial niche
2. Matching Flow: How parties find and connect with each other
3. Onboarding Structure: Per-side requirements and simplified MVP onboarding
4. Trust Framework: Trust mechanisms, eligibility rules, dispute handling
5. Payments/Transactions: Payment model, platform role in transactions
6. Launch Strategy: Seeding approach, manual interventions, imbalance monitoring
</a3_specific_sections>

<template_guidelines>
- Define at least 2 sides (e.g., buyers & sellers)
- Identify which side to seed first and why
- Keep matching flow simple for MVP - manual is OK
- Consider chicken-and-egg problem in launch strategy
- Trust features can be minimal but must exist
</template_guidelines>

<quantity_requirements>
- Must-have features: Generate 5-7 features (not 3), each linked to a Job from VPC
- Nice-to-have features: Generate 3-5 features deferred to later with clear deferral reasoning
- Critical workflows: Generate 3 essential user journeys with 5-8 detailed steps each
- Success metrics: Generate 3-4 quantitative metrics and 2 qualitative signals
- Assumptions: Generate 4 key assumptions with detailed risk analysis and mitigation
- Constraints: Generate 4-5 constraints across different categories
- Learning goals: Generate 3 specific learning goals
- Out of scope items: Generate 5-6 items that are explicitly excluded
</quantity_requirements>

<depth_requirements>
Feature descriptions (50-100 words each): Explain WHAT, HOW, edge cases, and user needs addressed.
Workflow steps (15-30 words each): Include user actions, system responses, timing, error handling.
Persona description (100-150 words): Demographics, daily routine, pain frequency, workarounds, emotional context.
Assumptions (detailed): State clearly, explain WHY it matters, quantify risk, provide actionable mitigation.
Purpose statement (75-100 words): Articulate validated problem with evidence, why NOW, business opportunity.
</depth_requirements>

<enum_values>
Use ONLY these exact values:
- job_type: "functional" | "emotional" | "social"
- primary_platform: "web" | "mobile" | "both" | "desktop" | "sms" | "ussd" | "voice" | "whatsapp" | "telegram" | "api" | "pos" | "kiosk" | "embedded"
- access_method: "login" | "link" | "access_code" | "public" | "sms_shortcode" | "ussd_code" | "phone_call" | "qr_code" | "api_key" | "oauth" | "biometric" | "pin" | "no_auth"
- output_type: "dashboard" | "report" | "alert" | "notification" | "export" | "message" | "sms" | "email" | "document" | "receipt" | "certificate" | "invoice" | "confirmation" | "response" | "file" | "api_response"
- constraint_category: "feature" | "integration" | "technical" | "compliance" | "scope" | "operational" | "resource" | "timeline" | "budget" | "regulatory" | "security" | "scalability" | "geographic"
- confidence: "low" | "medium" | "high"
</enum_values>

